[{"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "Oberfinanzdirektion BerlinStZBl-1988-1699EStK \u00a7 7 EStG Fach 3 Nr 1004EStG: 7OFD Berlin St 445 - S-2196 - 4/86 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "8 12 1993 EStK \u00a7 7 EStG Fach 3 Nr 1004OFD Berlin St 445 - S-2196 - 4/86 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "2 6 1994 EStK \u00a7 7 EStG Fach 3 Nr 1004 Breakdown of the purchase price for condominiums for income tax purposes according to table values \u200b\u200bTo breakdown the purchase price for condominiums in Berlin (West) in shares for the building as well as for the land I have developed a simplified procedure, which is to be applied in the context of income tax assessment without using the valuation and property tax offices"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "It is a mathematical procedure in which the individual values \u200b\u200bare calculated in accordance with the principles of the BFH judgment of January 15, 1985 (StZBl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "1415)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "The results were checked in a statistical procedure based on the purchase price allocations carried out in previous years"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "The tables created on the basis of the calculation take into account five different values \u200b\u200bfor differentiation: the living area, the co-ownership share, the size of the property, the year of construction, the land value"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "The information on 1 and 2 can be found in the tax files or by contacting the taxpayer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "The information on 3 to 5 will in future be noted by the valuation and property tax offices on the back of the copy of the sale notification intended for the purchaser's tax office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "If information is exceptionally missing, this can be requested by telephone or in writing from the valuation and property tax office responsible for the standard valuation of the condominium"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "These values \u200b\u200bcan be given to the taxpayer or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "his advisor can be informed upon request before the assessment is carried out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "After all the initial data are available, proceed as follows: The property size specified in square meters must be multiplied by the value of the co-ownership share in order to determine the size of the proportional property area corresponding to the co-ownership"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "Example: Total size of the property: 1200 sqm Co-ownership: 70/1000 Proportional property area: 1200 x 70: 1000 = 84 sqm The ratio of this proportionate property area to the living space must be calculated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "Example: Proportional property area: 84 sqm living area: 110 sqm living area: proportionate GrSt"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "area = 110: 84 = 131 result = 1: 131 This means that in this case table no 10 is to be used"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "The building age (age) is to be determined"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "The year of completion of the building (year of construction) must be deducted from the year of acquisition"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "Example: Year of purchase: 1986 Year of construction: 1934 Age: 1986 - 1934 = 52 years In the table under \"Age in years\" this value is to be found"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "It can be found at 50 - 54 years of age"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "In the column 50 - 54 years of age, look for the value that is assigned to the land price reported by the valuation and property tax office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "Example: Land price: 650 DM / sqm The corresponding table value can now be read off"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "For a land price of DM 600 to DM 699, table no. 10 shows a building value share of 84% for ages 50 - 54"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "The proportional value for the land is 16%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "The use of a tabular value and the underlying output data must be explained in an annex to the tax assessment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "The values \u200b\u200bin the table only apply to condominiums occupied in Berlin for transfers of ownership (transfer of charges) from January 1, 1984. If the taxpayer does not agree with the share of the value of the building determined in this way, or if an earlier date of purchase is to be taken into account, the valuation and property tax office of the tax office responsible for the unit valuation is to be taken into account to ask for administrative assistance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "This will then carry out a calculation according to the previous procedure (see Circular Order No. 118/85 EW No. 225 (1964)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "Administrative assistance should also be requested if the ratio of the proportionate property area is less than 1: 025 or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "is greater than 1:45 or if peculiarities of the case are recognizable which suggest that the building value share cannot be recorded in a standard calculation method (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "In addition to special and co-ownership, there is also a large degree of partial ownership or it is a question of subsequently created attic apartments)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "This circular is to be applied to all non-final assessment cases from the assessment period 1984 onwards"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "Insofar as the taxpayer is already aware of the individual value determinations as the basis for depreciation calculations, the determined values \u200b\u200bwill also remain in the future, unless the taxpayer requests the use of the tabular value"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "Addition for the valuation and property control centers: From now on, the following information must be given on the back of the sale notification (GrEStG 1e) intended for condominiums for owner-occupied apartments: Property size (total property size) Year of construction Land value (last guideline value in DM / sqm) requests for official assistance from F\u00c4 in the rest of Germany are still to be answered by the assessment and property control offices"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "In doing so, the above principles must be followed, with missing information being requested from the requesting FA"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "The system was not included"}, {"meta": {"name": "0085843.xml"}, "text": "--- Accounting income tax / wage tax / church tax Berlin"}]